"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The three pathways of complement activation are shown. Each leads to generation of activated C3b. The classical pathway is triggered by antibody interacting with antigen, and the lectin pathway by a lectin binding to a sugar. The alternative pathway turns over continuously. Activation of the complement system leads to inflammation (release of anaphylatoxins C3a and C5a), membrane perturbation and lysis (via the membrane attack complex, C5b-9), and opsonization (deposition of C3b and C4b).",
